\N<Boss-kun>Hm? Boku-chan, are you going home? Well then, I
guess we'll disband too.

\N<Boku>Wow, this is amazing! What could this be? Is it
someone's playground...? But there's no one here.... I

\N<Boku>It's already late, maybe I should come back another

\N<Boy>Hey you over there! Get off and come here!
\N<Boy>That's right. There's no one else, right?

\N<Boy>What's wrong? No way! You, did you just intrude into
our super top-secret secret base of the Princess Mountain
Defense Squad without permission!
\N<Boku>Huh!? Is this your secret base? That's amazing!

\N<Boy>...Not that! We won't forgive illegal intruders into
our base! And on top of that, knowing the secrets of our
secret base... We can't just let you go alive...
\N<Boku>Eh...! No way! I don't want to!

\N<Boy>If you don't like it, there's no other way. You'll
have to join the Princess Mountain Defense Squad too. If you
do that, you'll be able to enter the secret base too.

\N<Boku>Eh!? Is that so!? Yeah! Then, I also want to join
that something-something club!

\N<Boy>It's the Princess Mountain Defense Squad. However,
you can't join easily. You'll have to take a strict entrance
exam.

\N<Boy>That's right. If you can defeat me in a 'Bug Battle,'
I'll allow you to join.

\N<Boy>What's the matter, don't you know? It's the hottest
game right now where you make the beetles you caught, like
stag beetles and rhinoceros beetles, fight each other.
\N<Boku>Is that so... but I don't have any bugs...?

\N<Boy>I guess there's no other choice. Here, I'll lend you
this 'bug net,' so go ahead and catch something. I saw a
stag beetle around here earlier.
\N<Boku>Wow! Thanks! Then, I'll try catching one!

Obtained a plaything. When you have obtained a plaything,
you can switch between it using the W key and the Q key, and
use the item with the confirm button.

When you press the W key, it will switch in the order of
bare hands -> tool 1 -> tool 2 -> tool 3 -> bare hands. In
the case of the Q key, it will be the opposite.

You can catch bugs by using a bug net for insects and a
fishing rod for fish, depending on the target. However, you
cannot use playthings like these inside the house.

Furthermore, please note that you cannot talk to or examine
things while holding a tool. You can confirm the above
explanation in the instruction manual as well.

Let's quickly grab the 'bug net' and try catching the 'bugs'
flying around or perched on trees.

\N<Boy>If you swing a bug net towards bugs, you can catch
them. Bugs are small, so search carefully. They might be
flying around or shining black on trees.

\N<Boy>Oh? Did you catch a sawtooth stag beetle? Then let's
have a bug battle right away!
\N<Boku>Um... How do you play bug battles?

\N<Boy>Hmm... Listen carefully, the basics of bug battles
are like a one-on-one rock-paper-scissors game.

\N<Boy>That's right, rock-paper-scissors. There are four
commands you can give to bugs. Attack, special move,
barrier, and charge.

\N<Boku>Huh? Barrier...? Can bugs really do something like
that...?

\N<Boy>Use your imagination there. You play pretend games,
right? Even in a game of tag, can you really become the
demon?

\N<Boy>If you understand, then let's continue with the
explanation.

\N<Boy>First, attacks are strong against barriers, but weak
against special moves.

\N<Boy>Finishing moves are strong against attacks, but weak
against barriers.

\N<Boy>Barriers are strong against finishing moves, but weak
against attacks.

\N<Boy>And finally, Charge is weak against everything, but
it slightly restores the bug's stamina and increases its
attack power for the next turn.

\N<Boy>What you need to be careful of is that finishing
moves require 'move points' and can't be used when they run
out.
\N<Boy>Also, you can't give the same command twice in a row.

\N<Boy>This rule applies to both you and your opponent, so
think carefully about what the opponent will do next and
give instructions to the bug.

\N<Boy>The one who reduces the opponent's bug's HP to zero
first wins. Also, if the bug moves back due to an 'attack'
or 'finishing move', falling off the dohyo (sumo ring)
counts as a loss.

\N<Boy>Well, it would be faster to actually do it. Don't
worry, I'll go easy on you.

\N<Boy>Oh, don't forget that the bug at the front of your
team will participate in the battle. Well then, let's get
started quickly.

\N<Boy>Well, I guess there's no helping it. Listen
carefully.

During the Bug Battle, you can change the speed of the Bug
Battle by pressing the Shift key. When in Speed Up mode, a
music note symbol will be displayed in the upper left
corner.

Boy: Huh...? I don't have a bug... Let's battle with this
bug.

\N<Boy>Hmm... You're pretty good for a beginner. Alright, as
promised, I'll allow you to join the Hime-no-yama Defense
Squad.

\N<Boy>Too bad. But well, you did pretty well for a

Boy: I'm 'Boku'! Nice to meet you!
\N<Boy>Boku? That's a strange name. Well, whatever.

\N<Boss-kun>I am the captain of this defense squad. Call me
'Boss' or 'Captain'. After all, I am the oldest among the
boys around here.

wear glasses and seem smart, don't they? But they're younger
than me, unlike Boku-chan.

\N<Hakase-kun>Nice to meet you, Boku-kun. Let's get along

\N<Boss-kun>Next to Hakase is Boushi. They always wear their

as Hakase.

\N<Boss-kun>And the one in the back is Yuu. They're the same
age as me, Boku-chan.
Yuu-kun: Nice to meet you, Boku-kun.

\N<Boss-kun>And this little one here is 'Sacchan'. They're
the youngest among us.

\N<Boss-kun>Hmm? Is that so? Well then, I guess it's fine to
introduce them.

\N<Boss-kun>And finally, the most selfish girl in the
Defense Squad, 'Nana'. They're the same age as me, Boku-chan
and Yuu.

\N<Boss-kun>Since the other five, excluding Nana who hates

\N<Boss-kun>In bug battles, there are practice matches and
official matches. It's okay to lose in practice matches, but
if you lose in an official match, that bug will be exhausted
and unusable for the rest of the day, so be careful.

\N<Boss-kun>If you win a few times in official matches,
everyone will bring out their special bugs. Well, I don't
think it's possible, but if you can beat my special bug,

\N<Boss-kun>You guys should also give something to the

\N<Boss-kun>Oh, and one more thing! We're holding the Bug
Battle Tournament to determine who's the strongest Bug
Battler this year on the 25th! Don't forget, everyone! Boku-
chan will also be participating!
\N<Boss-kun>Well then, everyone can do as they please.

When you select Bug Cage from the menu, you can exchange
your current bugs. Additionally, when you select Bug
Training, you can use Training Points to level up your bugs.

If you don't have enough points for leveling up, you won't
be able to select it. Training Points accumulate when you
participate in bug battles or catch new bugs.
